data.name: LabelInformation.Text
data.value:
Welcome to the import dungeon brush wizard.
The next few screens will guide you through importing a new brush into your dungeon file. This will allow you to paint your dungeon using this new brush.
There are four screens:
General: Provide general information about the brush - comment, colour. Front Asset: Provide information about the front asset of the brush - foreground tile or object. Back Asset: Provide information about the back asset of tbe hrush - background tile. Rules: Provide rules for the brush - surface, clear.
You may exit the wizard at any time by pressing cancel.
You may add your brush at any time by pressing finish. Be warned: if you do not fill out all of the information for your brush, you may have to edit the dungeon file manually to complete it.
